Bold Tag makes the enclosed text bold
Use: [b]This is some text[/b]
This is some text

Center causes the selected text to be centered.
Use: [center]This is some centered text[/center]
This is some centered text

Code Tag
Blockquotes the text you reference and preserves formatting. Useful for displaying code.
Use: [code]This is formatted text[/code]

Font Colour Tag
Sets the text color, any named colour can be used.
Use: [XXX]This is XXX text[/XXX]
This is XXX text

LTR direction Tag: Wraps the selected text in span with dir=ltr. Useful for writing ltr text in an rtl based forum
Use: [ltr]This is some ltr text[/ltr]
This is some ltr aligned text

RTL direction Tag: Wraps the selected text in a span tag with dir=rtl. Useful for writing rtl text in an ltr based forum
Use: [rtl]This is some rtl text[/rtl]
This is some rtl text

Email Tag
turns an email address into a mailto hyperlink.
Use: [url=email@email.com]Link text[/url]

Font Tag
Sets the font face of the enclosed text.
Use: [font=XXX]The font of this text is XXX[/font=XXX]

Image Tag
Inserts an image into a post.
Use: [img]http://www.anywhere.com/image.gif[/img]

Italicise Tag makes the enclosed text italics
Use: [i]This is some italicised text[/i]
This is some italicised text

Align left causes the selected text to be aligned with the left edge.
Use: [left]This is some left aligned text[/left]
This is some left aligned text

Hyperlenke Tag
turns a url into a hyperlink.
Use: [url]http://www.anywhere.com[/url]
Use: [url=http://www.anywhere.com]Link text[/url]

Quote Tag
Quotes the enclosed text to reference something specific that someone has posted.
Use: [quote]This is a quote[/quote]

Align right causes the selected text to be aligned with the right edge.
Use: [right]This is some right aligned text[/right]
This is some right aligned text

Horizontal rule creates a horizontal line accros your post.
Use: [hr]

Font Size Tag
Sets the text size, possible values are 1 to 6, 1 being the smallest.
Use: [size=XXX]This is size XXX text[/size=XXX]

Strike-through causes the selected text to have a line drawn through it.
Use: [s]This is some stricken text[/s]
This is some stricken text

A subscript is a number, figure, symbol, or indicator that is smaller than their normal line of type and is set slightly below it.
Use: H[sub]2[/sub]O
H2O

A superscript is a number, figure, symbol, or indicator that is smaller than their normal line of type and is set slightly above it.
Use: y=mc[sup]2[/sup]
y=mc2
Table Tag adds a html table tag
Allows you to select the number of rows and columns for your table.

Underline Tag underlines the enclosed text

The forum will attempt to detect a users timezone and display times accordingly, However this is not always possible, so this option sets the default timezone for the forum. 
Datetimes will be displayed in this format by default. This may come in handy if you are located in one part of the world, and your server is in another, and you need the time displayed in the forum to be converted to a local time for you!
Choose the format you wish all dates to be displayed in. Default is 31/12/2018 (UK Short).

First, you must have Signatures enabled to use Dynamic Signatures. With Dynamic Signatures enabled, the users signature is not added to the post until it is viewed, so if a person changes their signature, that change will apply to all posts made by that user. But, this will only apply to posts made while Dynamic Signatures are enabled. Any signature that is already in a post won't be updated.

When a post is edited, there is an appending to the end of the post that says when and by whom the post was edited. Turning this function off would make it so that the footer would not be placed on the end of the post.

Disabling the E-mail function will turn off any features that involve sending mail. If you don't have an SMTP server of any type, you will want to turn this feature off. If you do have an SMTP (mail) server, however, then also select the type of server you have from the dropdown menu.

Do you want to require each user to validate their E-mail Address when they first Register and anytime they change their E-mail Address?
The user will receive an E-mail with a link in it that will validate that the E-mail Address they entered is a valid E-mail Address.
Allow your users to enter 2 of their Favorite Links, to be viewed in their profile.

This allows you to filter out E-mail addresses from a given domain - like all addresses from @example.com.
This will prevent people from registering with E-mail addresses at that domain.

With Flood Control enabled, normal users will have to wait the specified amount of time between posts before they can post again. 
Admins and Moderators are not affected by this limitation. 
Enter the number of seconds to wait.
Set the number of Topics to display in a Forum page, to enable multiple page size add a comma separated list of page sizes (10,20,40 etc.).

Group Categories enable you to 'group' Categories together into 'Groups' to better organize how Categories are displayed on your forum.

Hot Topics change the topic folder icon in the Forum view from a normal folder to a flaming folder to let people know that your minimum number of posts has been met to categorize this topic as one that is seeing a lot of action.
Allow users to post smiley faces and other icons allowed by the Forums within the body of their posts!
Turns On/Off features that allow users to enter their ICQ number... then for other users to send them ICQ messages and/or see if they are online.

Do you require a user to be logged on before being able to use the Send Topic To a Friend or E-mail Poster options?
Allow your users to enter their Marital Status, to be viewed in their profile.

Prevent users under the age you specify here from registering. The default is 13 for COPPA compliancy but you can change it to anything you want. To turn this feature off completely, set the minimum age to 0.
When enabled, this feature allows the Administrator or the Moderator to 'Approve', 'Hold' or 'Delete' a users post before it is shown to the public.
If enabled, this feature automatically sends an e-mail to the topic author if it is moved.
This feature either allows or dis-allows a Moderator of one forum to move topics within their forum to someone else's forum where they do not have moderator rights.
Turns On/Off features that allow users to enter their Skype username... then for other users to view their Skype Username.
Allow your users to enter their Occupation, to be viewed in their profile.
This is now only used for the Topic Paging, it limits the amount of pages shown in each row when a topic is more than one page long.

Allow your users to upload an Avatar, to be viewed in their profile and in all their posts.

Private Forums enable you to only allow certain members to see that the forum exists. If it's only password protected, everyone can see that it exists, however, they are prompted for a password to get in.

This allows you to choose who is able to register on your forum by approving or rejecting their registration.

This turns off or on the Format Section on the screen where your users post new topics/reply to existing topics.
[b]Note:[/b] You must also have Forum Code enabled on your forum to use this feature.

If this function is on, it shows the name of the moderator beside the forum that they moderate on the main default page. If it is off, however, visitors won't see who is moderating the forum they are posting in.
Quick Paging is when you have a topic that is more than 1 page, a small graphic and the #'s will be show next to the topic title so you can go straight to page 2 or 3, etc...

Turns On/Off the display of a Printer Friendly link that is shown when viewing a topic. This link will popup a window with the topic and any replies that are shown in a format that is easier to print.
Allows users to reply to a topic via a reply box at the bottom of the page when viewing a topic.

Turns On/Off the display of a Send Topic to a Friend Link that is shown when viewing a topic.. This link will allow a user to e-mail a topic to a friend. E-mail functions must be on for this link to show up.

Allows users to insert smilies in their posts by clicking on the smilie in a small table shown to them in the post screen.
[b]Note:[/b] You must also have Icons enabled on your forum to use this feature.

Turns On/Off the display of detailed statistics (last visited date and time, last post, active topics, newest member) at the bottom of the forum. When turned off, some statistics are displayed at the top of the page.
Turns On/Off the display of previous topic  and next topic  icons on the topics page.
Allows users to set a 'Signature' into their Posts. The same concerns mentioned for Images in Posts applies here as well.
Allow your users to enter their County/State, to be viewed in their profile.
Turns On/Off the ability of an Admin or Moderator to 'Stick' a post at the top of the Topics List. While this Topic is 'Sticky', it will remain at the top of the list.

Allows you to set the Highest Level of Subscription that can be used on the Forum. 
You will also need to set the individual level in each of your Categories and Forums.

Enter either a positive or negative integer value between +12 and 0 and -12. This may come in handy if you are located in one part of the world, and your server is in another, and you need the time displayed in the forum to be converted to a local time for you! (Default value is 0, meaning no adjustment)

Choose 24Hr to display all times in military (24 hour) format or 12Hr to display all times in 12 hour format appended with an AM or PM depending on whether it's before or after midday. Default is 24 hour.
